    • Constructor Detail

      • SBML2BioPAX

        public SBML2BioPAX()
        Constructor SBML2BioPAX.
        Main method of the biological model export from SBML (Systems Biology Markup Language) to BioPAX (Biological PAthway eXchange format). Provide it a file when you call the program with the command 
        java uk.ac.ebi.compneur.sbml2biopax.SBML2BioPAX <SBMLfile>
        JSBML is used to read and check the SBML file provided.
        Create the SBMLDocument object and start the creation of the Ontological BioPAX model.
        Save the BioPAX file in the same file path and name that the input file, but replace the extension by .owl.
        Parameters:
        theFile - Path of the SBML file to export

    • Method Detail

      • biopaxexport

        public BioPAXModel biopaxexport(SBMLModel sbmlmodel)
                         throws org.sbml.jsbml.SBMLException
        Converts a SBML model into a BioPax Model.

        Use JSBML to read the SBML model, and Paxtools to write the BioPax model in OWL.
        The conversion is composed of different parts:

        • fill the Maps coming from the configuration file. They will be use to determine the specific Biopax class of the translated SBML elements.
        • 'model' translation into a BioPax pathway: source on BioModels database, taxonomy, publication references
        • compartments treatment
        • species treatment (following the BioPAX classes: complex, dna, rna, protein, smallMolecule). The Algorithm take care about the constraint. For example a annotation about KEGG will be typing in a smallMolecule class. But the annotation "http://www.genome.jp/kegg/compound/#C00039" describe the Deoxyribonucleotide. A second loop replace the term in dna.
          The Ensembl annotation is special, due to the two first terms of the identifier indicating the type dna, rna or protein of the species. ex: http://www.ensembl.org/#ENSRNOG -> dna ; ENSRNOT -> rna ; ENSRNOP -> protein
        • reaction parsing, and creation of the physicalInteraction subclasses. If the reaction contain one or several modifier, they are translate in a control or a catalysis (if contain a EC Code). The reactants and products part are translated in biochemicalReaction as default value. If they contain several compartment and annotations for the same species, the conversion is change for a transport. If the number of species between the reactant and product is different and the annotation correspond to a complex, the conversion is change to a complexAssembly
        Parameters:
        sbmlModel - SBML object create with the path provide to the constructor
        Returns:
        biopaxModel BioPAX ontology corresponding to the SBML exported
        Throws:
        org.sbml.jsbml.SBMLException
